data.chText: 他脖子上挂着圆形身份牌。
data.enText: He wears an identity disc around his neck.

data.chText: 这录音有激光唱片和盒式磁带两种。
data.enText: This recording is available on disc or cassette.
a structure made of cartilage between the bones of the back

data.chText: 他因椎间盘突出一直未上班。
data.enText: He's been off work with a slipped disc (= one that has moved from its correct position, causing pain) .

tr: (computer science) a memory device consisting of a flat disk covered with a magnetic coating on which information is stored
sound recording consisting of a disk with a continuous groove
used to reproduce music by rotating while a phonograph needle tracks in the groove
something with a round shape resembling a flat circular plate
example: the moon's disk hung in a cloudless sky

value.boxr_value: The spelling disk is also used in American English, mainly for meaning 1. 美国英语中亦拼作disk，主要用于义项1。

value.def: A disc is a flat, circular shape or object.

example.ex: Most shredding machines are based on a revolving disc fitted with replaceable blades.
example.tran: 大多数粉碎机都是基于一个装有可替换刀片的旋转圆盘来实现作业的。

value.def: A disc is one of the thin, circular pieces of cartilage which separates the bones in your back.

example.ex: I had slipped a disc and was frozen in a spasm of pain.
example.tran: 我有一个椎间盘错位了，疼得我动弹不得。

value.def: A disc is a record that you play on a record player.

example.ex: This disc includes the piano sonata in C minor.
example.tran: 这张唱片包括了 C小调的钢琴奏鸣曲。

trans: 激光唱片，光盘(缩略形式为CD)
(电台、电视台、俱乐部)唱片节目主持人
金唱片(颁发给唱片销售量特别大的歌手或乐队)
(给唱片销售量极高的歌手等颁发的)白金唱片
(颁发给唱片销售量超过一定数量的歌手或乐队的)银唱片
(贴在汽车、摩托车上的)圆形纳税凭证
